<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="153" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1256,1563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,421,1256,1282]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Nomenclatural notes:—</emphasis>
<materialsCitation collectionCode="U, M" collectorName="Martius &amp; Berg &amp; Villavicencio" location="Brazilian Amazon region" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" specimenCode="U0004677" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="holotype">
In the protologue is not stated the herbarium where the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miquel" authorityYear="1847" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" form="major" genus="Urostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="form" species="cestrifolium">
<emphasis box="[1119,1378,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Urostigma cestrifolium</emphasis>
forma 
<emphasis box="[136,203,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was deposited, it only reports that the species was collected by 
<emphasis box="[911,1000,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">
<collectorName box="[911,1000,1292,1317]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Martius</collectorName>
</emphasis>
in the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:D92A87FDFFA5C66CFF375138FF71F9B9:545C6030FFA5C66CFB8C5068FADAFA87" box="[1075,1359,1291,1317]" name="Brazilian Amazon region" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Brazilian Amazon region</location>
. 
<collectorName box="[1369,1423,1292,1318]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Berg</collectorName>
&amp; 
<collectorName box="[136,285,1326,1352]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Villavicencio</collectorName>
(2004) cited as the type (in the work as “ 
<typeStatus box="[742,847,1326,1353]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">holotype</typeStatus>
”) the material deposited in the 
<collectionCode box="[1193,1213,1327,1353]" country="Netherlands" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15513" name="Nationaal Herbarium Nederland" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" type="Herbarium">U</collectionCode>
herbarium, however, this cannot be considered a lectotypification because it was published after 2001 and the “designated here” or a similar phrase was not used (
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[377,598,1397,1423]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" refId="ref7456" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="proceedings" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[474,531,1397,1423]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
, Art. 7.11). We did not find a duplicate in the Munich Herbarium (
<collectionCode box="[1348,1377,1397,1423]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15637" name="Botanische Staatssammlung München" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" type="Herbarium">M</collectionCode>
). Here we designate the material 
<specimenCode box="[432,550,1432,1458]" collectionCode="U" country="Netherlands" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15513" name="Nationaal Herbarium Nederland" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" type="Herbarium">U0004677</specimenCode>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[632,735,1432,1458]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">lectotype</typeStatus>
because it is the only material found and is in accordance with the description of the protologue
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1256,1563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,453,1502,1528]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Taxonomical notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[453,746,1502,1528]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" form="major" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="form" species="cestrifolia">
<emphasis box="[453,640,1502,1528]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Ficus cestrifolia</emphasis>
f. 
<emphasis box="[679,746,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was synonymized by Berg &amp; Villavicencio (2004) as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pertusa">Ficus pertusa</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
